timeline
    title EU AI Act Enforcement Timeline (Regulation 2024/1689, updated with Digital Omnibus)
    section 2024
        1 Aug 2024  : Published in Official Journal of the EU
                    : Act enters into force (12 Jul 2024)
    section 2025
        2 Feb 2025  : ✅ Prohibited AI practices apply (Art. 5)
                   : ✅ AI literacy obligations (Art. 4)
                   : Fines up to €35M / 7% turnover for prohibited practices
        2 Aug 2025  : ✅ GPAI model obligations apply (Art. 53–55)
                   : ✅ GPAI Code of Practice published (10 Jul 2025)
                   : ✅ Governance & penalties chapters apply
    section 2026
        2 Feb 2026  : ✅ Commission guidelines on high-risk classification (Art. 6)
        2 Nov 2026  : Art. 50 transparency obligations apply
                   : AI-generated content watermarking requirements
                   : National AI regulatory sandboxes must be operational
    section 2027
        2 Aug 2027  : Legacy GPAI models must comply
        2 Dec 2027  : High-risk AI obligations apply (Annex III)
                   : Full Title III requirements for new high-risk systems
                   : Deadline set by Digital Omnibus (trilogue Apr 2026)
    section 2028
        2 Aug 2028  : High-risk AI in regulated products (Art. 6.1)
                   : Medical devices, machinery, vehicles, etc.
    section 2030
        2 Aug 2030  : Legacy public sector AI systems must comply
        31 Dec 2030 : Large-scale IT system AI components must comply
